Unidirectional OW3D initial-condition batch
Updated: 19-Mar-2026 02:06:08

Purpose
Generate unidirectional OW3D initial conditions with OW3D kinematics output enabled in the settings file for downstream surface-kinematics checks.

What this batch is trying to verify
- This batch is intended to provide one OW3D-ready subdirectory per unidirectional test case with OW3D kinematics storage enabled.
- Use these cases to inspect OW3D kinematics output alongside the usual surface elevation and surface potential outputs.
- The Section 8 settings now request one x-z kinematics plane spanning the full x-range at the single y index of the unidirectional domain.

Current workflow
- Direct MF12 unidirectional reconstruction for each generated phase/state combination.
- OW3D Section 8 is configured to save both surface output and one kinematics plane per case.
- The requested kinematics plane spans the full x-range at the only y-index of the unidirectional setup.
- One subdirectory per generated case.

Current settings snapshot
- output directory = uni initial condition\ow3d_kinematics_check
- phases = [0, 90, 180, 270] deg
- kd/Alpha pairs = [(kd=1.00, Alpha=1.0)]
- t_init = -20.00 Tp
- duration = 40.00 Tp
- domain length = 15313.857 m
- grid = [4097 x 1], dx = 3.739 m
- surface stride = 8
- OW3D kinematics enabled = true
- OW3D kinematics flag = 20
- OW3D kinematics files = 1
- OW3D kinematics time stride = 8
